Pampered myself with a Cryotherapy Facial at @ameon.skin and your sis was glowing. My skin felt refreshed, supple and smooth afterwards!

I never went through the acne phase as a teenager. But since I’ve turned 40 I’ve been dealing with hormonal cystic acne on my chin. I’ve gotten it somewhat under control with a rigorous skincare routine which includes Tretinoin and Hydroquinone to help fade the acne scarring, along with monthly chemical peels from my derm. I’ll be adding cryotherapy to my regularly routine.

Do you suffer from severe itching and irritation after getting braids? You’re probably allergic to the alkaline base that’s sprayed on the hair to keep it from molding. Soak the hair in apple cider vinegar and warm water, rinse and hang to air dry.

Also, I cut my Xpressions Ultra Braid into three to get the most out of a single pack, then stretch it out to thin the ends. If you want your braids super long (like knee caps), then cut the braid in half and stretch. Happy braiding 😘

Can you braid your own hair? I’ve been braiding my hair myself since I was 12 years old. I braid my hair underhanded. While I braid other people’s hair overhanded. But I braid my own hair in reverse as I’m able to get a tighter grip, and braid more comfortably this way.

Side note- Any style that I do on other peoples hair, I practice on my own head first ☺️

Have you guys ever tried green seasoning? It seems as if most Caribbean countries have their own version. The only good thing that came  out of my relationship with my ex is learning how to make this Trini Green Seasoning from his mama 😝

Wish I were here right now ☺️. Throwback to my visit to the @mayan_clay_spa_bathhouse in Tulum during my 40th Birthday Solo Trip. I treated myself to the 2 Hour Healing Clay & Swedish Oil Massage Combo and it was a divine experience. First I took a warm outdoor shower and was then led to a huge outdoor massage cabana where I received a one hour massage with warm clay to detox the body… To the sound of birds chirping, water fountains and serene music. It was so relaxing. Next I took another outdoor shower to wash off the clay after letting it dry. And finally I received another one hour massage with oils. Best massage of my life and bests believe I’m going back next time I’m in Tulum. Have you ever had a clay massage?

I’m celebrating myself on this International Women’s Day. The first quarter of 2023 has been a whirlwind. But I’m still standing tall and strong through it all 💪🏾 

A year ago I decided that I would be leaving NYC when my lease was up. 

As the new year rolled in I wasn’t sure that I could  do it and almost got cold feet. 

But I pushed through and started looking for an apartment which is a hard task when doing it long distance. 

I was approved for my dream apartment in an amazing community just when I thought I wouldn’t find anything. 

I started packing up my place well in advance in order to avoid being overwhelmed at the last minute. And still ended up overwhelmed and packing while the truck was being loaded. 

I moved in the midst of a crazy rainstorm which turned into a horrendous snowstorm once up north. 

But in the end, I made the move. 

I’m extremely proud of myself for stepping out on Faith and not letting fear get in the way of my goals and dreams. I’m excited to embark on this new journey. 

The next few months will be hectic as I’ll be transitioning into living in a new city. I’m actually still clearing out and cleaning my NYC apartment. 

Best of all I’ll be sharing my new journey with y’all. In fact, I’ve already started. If you’re not subscribed to my YouTube channel, then you’re missing out. Link in bio or search GlamMzMore😘

A big thanks to all of you guys that’s been sending me so much love and well wishes. I appreciate you 🫶🏾

My first time diffusing my natural hair and I’m mad I waited so long to try it. My curls came out elongated, full & fluffy and my hair is holding the shape better. Even after sleeping wild. 

I usually air dry and it takes my hair up to two days to completely dry since it’s so thick. Even longer in my new apartment as it’s humid. When I sleep on my hair while it’s wet, the curls get flat and I mess up the shape. I was tired of sleeping cute and getting a stiff neck trying not to mess up my hair. If you know then you know 😅

My hair still took like 10 years to dry using the diffuser lol. But at least I was able to sleep comfortably and wake up with my hair in tact. I’m sold and never air drying my wash n goes again.

How to refresh your chrome steering wheel emblem without buying a new airbag. If your emblem is looking beat down, then you can paint it with a liquid chrome paint pen to bring it back to life. Mistakes can be easily cleaned up with a little alcohol on a cotton swab. 

Otherwise you’ll have to buy a new airbag to safely replace the emblem, which costs a pretty penny. Some suggests to cut off the emblem and glue a new one on. This is not safe as it will leave plastic pins in the steering wheel which can injure you if God forbid you’re in an accident that deploys the airbag. Don’t do it. 

DM me “chrome” for a link to this Liquid Chrome Paint Pen.

The year is almost done. Have you had your annual mammogram? I had my second mammogram done at @akiracaresny Medical Imaging + Wellness and it was such an amazing experience. Especially compared to my first mammogram last year, which was cold and uncomfortable, and the tech was extremely rough with me. 

Not at Akira. The facility felt more like a spa than a doctor’s office. The decor was perfect from the color scheme and affirmations, to the elegantly depicted breasts wall paper. There’s individual changing rooms and lockers to store your belongings. You get to choose from an assortment of essential oil tabs to stick on your gown to help you relax. I chose Lavendar + Frankincense. 

The technicians were gentle and soft spoken, and explained every step of the procedures. I have dense breasts so I need to get an ultrasound along with my mammogram for a more thorough view, and even the gel used for the ultrasound was warm. 

Akira uses SmartCurve paddles which are more comfortable since the paddle is curved to fit the shape of your breasts, and not flat. Although the pressure was still a bit uncomfortable, it wasn’t painful like my first mammogram. 

The tea bar and healthy snack station was a nice finishing touch to my visit. 

Akira got everything right, and I wish that all imaging centers catered to us in this way to make us feel relaxed and comfortable during a procedure which is naturally uncomfortable and scary. I’ll be recommending Akira Medical Imaging + Wellness to everyone I know 💞
